Sea Rose

Waste the sea rose,  

you eager flower  
z tossed upon the wave—  

hold it toward your breast,  

sure of an answer,  

eclipse me in the light—  

are you lone?  

Are you lost?  

boast of the line’s  

amply measured  
growl  

of the tide.


- HD
